news.title: Goa town planning department clears zone changes for 15 plots in three talukas
news.para: The TCP department will alter the RP 2021 using the Goa TCP Act’s Section 39A, which allows the department to change the zoning of a plot based on applications from the owners.

news.title: After 11 years, Chandigarh housing board to repair Dhanas colony
news.para: CHB has initiated the process to allot the work to a firm. The work, estimated to cost around Rs 71 lakh, will include repair of column beams, damaged flooring and dismantled plaster in the common areas of the buildings, including roof.

news.title: Fourth-floor policy on hold, Haryana government tells HC; next hearing on September 3
news.para: On July 2, Haryana decided to allow construction of four floors, a move that raised significant concerns over the city's infrastructure. Gurgaon Citizens Council (GCC), a residents' group, approached the high court challenging the policy.

news.title: Karnataka cabinet approves measures to address land valuation inconsistencies
news.para: The `12,690 crore project, costing about `705 crore per kilometre, will initially build an 18.5-kilometre double-decker tunnel.  A `9.45 crore detailed project report (DPR) is expected by September, after which tenders will be issued for construction.

news.title: Karnataka RERA appoints Rakesh Singh as its chairman
news.para: Singh has previously worked as the head of the water resources department, administrator for BBMP, and also as additional chief secretary of the urban development department (UDD).

news.title: Ciena leases 1.35 lakh sq ft space in TRIL Tower in Gurugram
news.para: "A lot of space that was part of the SEZ is getting denotified now, opening up newer areas for corporations," one of them said. "Tata also has a large portfolio under SEZ and is getting it denotified."

news.title: Ghaziabad: Raj Nagar Extension still waiting to get basics right
news.para: Today, those living in the area aren’t worried about inter-city connectivity. It’s the basics that they demand. From no water supply to bumpy roads, there’s a lot that needs to be developed here, residents say.

news.title: Asia Opportunities V sells 3% stake in PNB Housing for Rs 676 crore
news.para: ​As per the bulk deal data available on the BSE, Asia Opportunities V (Mauritius) divested 78 lakh shares or a 3 per cent stake in PNB Housing Finance at Rs 866.70 apiece, taking the deal value to Rs 676.02 crore.

news.title: Delhi: Over 1,100 people registered in two DDA housing schemes on first day
news.para: According to the officials, 750 people registered in Sasta Ghar Housing Scheme 2024, and 405 registered in DDA Madhyam Vargiya Housing Scheme 2024 on the first day of the registration on Thursday.

news.title: Adani group promoters may sell 3% shares in Ambuja Cement for $500 million
news.para: Promoters will sell about 7 crore shares, or 2.84 per cent, in the cement maker for Rs 4,198 crore, sources aware of the matter said. The offer price of Rs 600 apiece is at a 5 per cent discount to Thursday's closing price of Rs 632.90 on BSE.

news.title: Cement manufacturers in India to invest Rs 1.25 lakh crore in FY25-27: Report
news.para: During this period, the industry is expected to add 130 million tons of cement grinding capacity, which is a fifth of the existing capacity.

news.title: Home registrations in Kolkata drop by 13% in July 2024
news.para: Home sale registrations in Kolkata saw an 18% decline in July, influenced by the state government's removal of incentives such as a stamp duty cut and reduction in circle rates. The Bengal chapter of Credai has requested a reconsideration, arguing that lower stamp duties would boost sales and contribute to the state exchequer.

news.title: PwC China may face six month business ban over Evergrande audit: Sources
news.para: A fine of at least 400 million yuan ($56 million) is expected to accompany the six-month ban, three of the people said. Combined with the business suspension, it would be the toughest ever penalty received by a Big Four accounting firm in China, the three people added.

news.title: Licences for old commercial buildings will continue to be renewed: Kerala minister
news.para: The decision came in response to a complaint from Ashwathi BS of Attingal, who reported difficulties in obtaining a commercial licence for an establishment operating in a building constructed before the regulations came into effect.

news.title: Goa urban development minister directs civic bodies to take services online
news.para: Vishwajit Rane, the urban development minister, directed all municipalities to provide their civic services online within 15 days. He instructed chief officers to inspect their jurisdictions and identify unused funds for utilization. Rane also discussed regularizing contractual municipal employees and announced nearly complete GIS mapping for North Goa towns, with similar plans for South Goa.

news.title: Interarch Building Products' IPO gets subscribed over 93.46 times on last day
news.para: The portion for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) received 205.41 times subscription while the quota for Non-Institutional Investors fetched 128.42 times subscription. The Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) part got subscribed 19.11 times.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group forecasts bigger net loss in H1 2024
news.para: China's property sector, a key driver of the economy, has been in turmoil since 2021, with housing sales plummeting 6.5% in 2023 from the previous year and 35.9% from its 2021 peak, following a regulatory crackdown on high leverage among developers that sparked a liquidity crisis.

news.title: KTR demands Telangana government to demolish illegal farmhouses in lake buffer zones
news.para: ​​KTR said he took the farmhouse from his friend on lease. He asserted that if this leased property is in violation of any regulations, it should be demolished.

news.title: South Korea holds interest rate amid property concerns
news.para: The Bank of Korea held its benchmark interest rate at 3.50% at its monetary policy review, as expected by 38 out of 40 economists surveyed by Reuters.

news.title: Developers struggle to find quality contractors amid housing boom
news.para: Many developers are boosting in-house capabilities while some are getting global contractors to ensure there is no delay in project delivery, industry insiders told ET. Some are also engaging construction tech companies.
